# The Ardent Companies — Marketing Website

> **Source of truth:** `AGENTS.md` (edit that first, then keep this file aligned).
> **Cline:** `.clinerules` is a symlink to this file.
> **Claude:** `CLAUDE.md` → `@AGENTS.md`.
> **Session log:** `JOURNAL.md`.

## Project Overview

A single-page, static Next.js marketing website for The Ardent Companies, a privately held real estate investment firm.

## Tech Stack

- Framework: Next.js 16.2.10 (with breaking changes — always check `node_modules/next/dist/docs/` before writing Next.js code)
- UI Library: React 19.2.4
- Styling: Tailwind CSS v4 (CSS-first config via `@import "tailwindcss"` and `@theme inline` in globals.css — do NOT create tailwind.config.ts)
- Language: TypeScript 5
- Fonts: System font Verdana (stack: Verdana, Geneva, sans-serif) — no Google Fonts imports
- Linting: ESLint 9 + eslint-config-next

## File Structure

- `src/app/layout.tsx` — Root layout with metadata and HTML structure
- `src/app/page.tsx` — Home page composing all sections in order
- `src/app/globals.css` — Tailwind import, CSS custom properties, @theme, type @utility classes
- `src/components/` — Header, Hero, Stats, Platforms, MarketPresence, Team, News, Contact, Footer, SvgImg
- `src/data/` — news.ts (LinkedIn fallbacks), team.ts (members, departments, bios)
- `src/lib/` — linkedin.ts (LinkedIn Posts API fetch + getNewsPosts() helper)
- `public/images/` — Static assets (`logo.svg`, `hero-bg.png`, `map-us.svg`, `map-uk.svg`, platform/news/team photos)
- `public/images/team/` — 38 individual headshots for team member cards

## Design System

### Colors (from globals.css)

- ardent-blue: #00315b
- ardent-blue-dark: #002a4d
- ardent-light: #f6f9fc
- charcoal: #4a4a4a
- background: #ffffff
- foreground: #00315b

Prefer tokens over one-off hex. Register new intentional colors in `:root` + `@theme inline`.

### Typography

**Font**: `Verdana, Geneva, sans-serif` only.

**Design intent**: Major Third (1.25). See full table in `AGENTS.md`.

**Implemented utilities** (use these in components):

| Class | Size |
| ----- | ---- |
| `text-hero` | `clamp(1.75rem, 5vw, 4.125rem)` |
| `text-heading-1` | `clamp(1.75rem, 3vw, 3rem)` |
| `text-heading-2` | `clamp(1.5rem, 2.5vw, 2.25rem)` |
| `text-heading-3` | `clamp(1.25rem, 1.75vw, 1.375rem)` |
| `text-body` | `1.125rem` (18px) |
| `text-body-lg` | `clamp(1.125rem, 1.5vw, 1.25rem)` |
| `text-small` | ~15.75px |
| `text-caption` | 14px — metadata only, not body copy |
| `text-stat` / `text-stat-lg` / `text-stat-accent` | clamp ranges for Stats |

Rules: rem/clamp only; body ≥16px; line-height ~1.5 body / ~1.2 headings; no Google Fonts.

### Layout Conventions

- Sections: `px-8.5` (34px) or `px-25` (100px); major vertical `py-30` (120px); mobile often `max-lg:px-6 max-lg:py-20`
- Cards: `rounded-[20px]` only (NO `rounded-[26px]`)
- Max content: `max-w-300` (1200px) mx-auto
- Gaps: `gap-7.5` (30px), `gap-2.5`, `gap-10`
- Prefer Tailwind v4 mapped utilities; arbitrary values when needed

## Critical Rules

1. **THIS IS NOT STANDARD NEXT.JS** — Next.js 16.2.10 has breaking changes. Read `node_modules/next/dist/docs/` before writing framework APIs.
2. **No client components** — Fully static, server-rendered. NO `"use client"`, NO useState/useEffect, NO event handlers beyond anchor links unless explicitly requested.
3. **Images** — `next/image` for JPG/PNG. Bare `<img>` OK for SVGs (`logo.svg`, `map-us.svg`, `map-uk.svg`). Prefer `sizes` on `fill` images.
4. **Single-page navigation** — Anchors: `#at-a-glance`, `#platforms`, `#presence`, `#team`, `#news`, `#contact`. Each section sets its `id`.
5. **Tailwind v4 CSS-first** — Colors/fonts via `@theme inline` in globals.css. Do NOT create tailwind.config.ts.
6. **All text is Verdana** — Single font via `font-sans`. No Archivo/PT Sans/Noto.
7. **Responsive design required** — Use `max-lg:` so multi-column layouts collapse below 1024px; reduce padding on small screens.
8. **New components** go in `src/components/`, PascalCase, default-exported, composed in `src/app/page.tsx`.
9. **Props** use inline type annotations.
10. **Gradient overlays** on images use absolute positioning; prefer tokenized brand blues.

## Component Reference

- **Header** — Sticky nav, logo (SVG img), 5 nav links, Investor Login, Contact Us CTA
- **Hero** — Background image, gradient overlay, H1 + description
- **Stats** — At a Glance large number stats
- **Platforms** — Debt + Equity cards with image backgrounds
- **MarketPresence** — US + UK maps
- **Team** — Leadership grid + working department tabs + bio modal (client component)
- **News** — Async LinkedIn Posts API integration with curated fallbacks
- **Contact** — Investing / Partnering / Working + Headquarters
- **Footer** — Copyright bar

